        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): reject Feishu announce jobs without target",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nReject creation of Feishu/Lark announce cron jobs when `delivery.to` is missing.\n\nThis fixes a case where cron accepted a job that could be stored and scheduled but would later fail at runtime during delivery with:\n\n```text\nDelivering to Feishu requires target <chatId|user:openId|chat:chatId>\n```\n\nCloses #39599.\n\n## What changed\n\n- add gateway/service-side validation in `src/cron/service/jobs.ts`\n- add CLI fail-fast validation in `src/cli/cron-cli/register.cron-add.ts`\n- add tests covering:\n  - Feishu without target → rejected\n  - Lark without target → rejected\n  - Feishu with explicit target → accepted\n\n## Why both layers\n\nGateway-side validation is the real safety boundary and prevents invalid jobs from entering the system through any creation path.\n\nCLI-side validation improves user feedback and fails earlier with a clearer message.\n\n## Validation\n\nRan:\n\n```bash\npnpm test src/cron/service.jobs.test.ts src/cron/normalize.test.ts\n```\n\nResult:\n- 2 test files passed\n- 64 tests passed\n",
